params.name: data.valid
params.description: Whether the provided user response token is valid. When valid = false, the reason could be specified in invalid_reason or it could also be due to a user failing to solve a challenge or a sitekey mismatch (i.e the sitekey used to generate the token was different than the one specified in the assessment).

params.name: data.invalid_reason
params.description: Reason associated with the response when valid = false.

params.name: data.create_time
params.description: The timestamp corresponding to the generation of the token.

params.name: data.hostname
params.description: The hostname of the page on which the token was generated.
